    • generatePathBetween2PointsWithGreedyMova

      private Flight generatePathBetween2PointsWithGreedyMova​(LongLat currentPosition, LongLat destination, java.util.ArrayList<Buildings> bL)
      generate flight path between 2 points by greedy move, for each move, I pick a valid angle that can make next position closest to destination ,this may cause local optimal problem, if the flight have too many number of moves, it means it meet this problem, then I will stop it and the returned flight will contain a signal 999 to show this solution is stuck, should try other generate method.
      Parameters:
      currentPosition - current position of drone
      destination - the position that drone want to go
      bL - the list of no-fly-zone buildings
      Returns:
      the generated flight path

    • generateGreedysolution

      public void generateGreedysolution​(java.util.ArrayList<Orders> orderList, java.util.ArrayList<Buildings> bl) throws java.io.IOException, java.lang.InterruptedException
      This method use greedy algorithm to generate solution. Each time,we chose the order that itself have highest monetary/moves ratio, and remove it from order list, we repeat this process until all orders delivered or drone's battery only allow it used to return to appleton tower.
      Parameters:
      orderList - the input order list
      bl - the list of no-fly-zone buildings
      Throws:
      java.io.IOException - IOException
      java.lang.InterruptedException - InterruptedException
